import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="state", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Count of Cities')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of cities across different states?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    city_count = data['city'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=city_count.index, y=city_count.values, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the most common city in the dataset?')
    plt.xlabel('City')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.axhline(city_count.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Most common city: {city_count.index[0]} ({city_count.max():.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="state", hue="city", data=data, palette="Set2")
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Count of Cities')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities in each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.kdeplot(data=data, x='lon', y='lat', fill=True, cmap='coolwarm', levels=20, thresh=0.05)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities based on their latitude and longitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
